  <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
  <p>This Cookie Policy explains how Pacific Ocean Tech uses cookies and similar technologies on our website.</p>

  <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
  <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help sites function, remember preferences, and understand usage.</p>

  <h2>Types we use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strictly necessary:</strong> Required for security, load balancing, and basic navigation.</li>
    <li><strong>Functional:</strong> Remember theme preferences (e.g., light/dark mode) and form progress.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Help us understand traffic and improve content (e.g., page views, referrers). We aim to use privacy-respecting analytics where possible.</li>
    <li><strong>Marketing (if enabled):</strong> Measure campaign performance and retargeting, only with consent where required.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
  <p>Embedded tools such as Calendly scheduling, video players, or social widgets may set their own cookies governed by those providers' policies.</p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p>You can control cookies through browser settings—blocking cookies may affect site functionality. Where required by law, we will request consent before non-essential cookies load.</p>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>We may revise this policy as our site evolves. Check this page for the latest version.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>privacy@pacificoceantech.com</p>
</LegalLayout>
